#4900
A dark cave~
The light from the hole in the ceiling does little to brighten this cave.
Small torches are lit along the walls, but they only make the shadows deeper
rather than chase them away. The floor of the cavern is covered in muck and
slime, making your footing unsteady. Foul smells best left unknown turn your
stomach and leave you feeling dizzy. As you look around what could only be
described as a living hell, one thought enters your mind - Home sweet home.
 
The cavern continues into darkness south of you. A large crack, just big
enough for a goblin to fit through, is in the west wall.
~
